NAME
    sort - sort lines of text

SYNOPSIS
    sort [-rnu] [file]

DESCRIPTION
    Sorts lines of text alphabetically or numerically.
    Reads from file or stdin if no file specified.

OPTIONS
    -r      Reverse the sort order
    -n      Sort numerically instead of alphabetically
    -u      Output only unique lines (remove duplicates)

EXAMPLES
    sort /tmp/list.txt
        Sort alphabetically

    sort -r /tmp/list.txt
        Sort in reverse order

    sort -n /tmp/numbers.txt
        Sort numerically

    find . | sort -u
        Sort and remove duplicates

SEE ALSO
    uniq, head, tail
